The paper deals with object localization in images using deep learning models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves incorporating prior knowledge and using entropy measures, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions medical image analysis, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM), and discusses image classification and retrieval, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR).
